{
  "stem": "13079.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I talk about abolished by federal statute, the statute law of this country is embodied in the process of enforcing war crimes, because that's the standard of this particular combatant.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when the different countries entered into the conventions, the Hague Convention of 1907 and the Geneva Convention of 1929, Germany was also a signatory to that convention.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And those two conventions-- the-- the Hague Convention really concerned itself with the duty on the part of combatants toward the civilian population.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the Geneva Convention concerned itself with combatants' treatments of their enemy, other combatants.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So that we had two particulars to the charge which was for violation of the laws and usages of war.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "One embodied the requirements on the country with respect to combatants and-- on the Geneva Convention, and-- with respect to noncombatants under the Hague Convention.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in that way, we put together a charge which was used to bring these individuals to the bar of justice.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Witnesses.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm glad you raised that point.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Witnesses came from every country in Europe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were some Americans that were in the camps, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that meant that those that were able to, after the armistice, they went back home and scattered.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we were given the means for ferrying these people back to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had accommodations there in Dachau for the witnesses that were away from home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was quite a chore and quite an undertaking to collect these witnesses, because those that were physically able did try to go back to their homes, and they'd scattered all over Europe.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we had a plane that was available to us-- a DC-3 that we used to ferry witnesses from different parts of Europe down to Munich.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, no, no, well--",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
